=Description=

"Richard Stallman gave a general, and mostly non-technical, talk about the development of the GNU operating system, the GPL, the justifications of free software, and the mortifications of proprietary software. When this cameraman asked whether there might be a 'free' video codec that would be acceptable for webcast - theora was recommended. Here you have the whole speech, plus a small sample highlight - an appearance of St IGNUcius -

